Well, I've been horrible glitches while playing MegaMan 3 on my NES (the real game, not trough emulation).<br />Not only the infamous scanline above ShadowMan does glitch, but, while fighting the first form of Dr.Willy, the screen mess up totally and glitch. You show the ground flickering A LOT where Willy's machine is, and, if you open the menu, the menu will be flickering where the Willy's machine is. There should be a problem with IRQs.<br />Honnestly, this is really crap for a licenced official game. Has this happened to anyone before (I think it's something with the PAL version of the game). Has anyone any idea why it's there ?<br />I've always trough MM3 was a great game, but now, I think it's by far the works MegaMan game on the NES. It has too many glitches, and this one does screw the whole thing up.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> â€” Fri Aug 19, 2005 1:32 pm</p><hr />
